"One has to learn to keep their addictions in check. And what am I addicted to? eating, vomiting, coke on the weekends and a glass of red wine to relax. That does not make me a bad person. I will work through my weaknesses, and my life is better than 95% of the people out there. My parents are still married, AND still in love. My sister is alive and in love and loves me. My half brother and half sister are alive, and they love me, and they have produced three offspring between the two of them, with another on the way next week, and they are happy and healthy and working hard to better their situations in life. I am not fat, I am not too skinny, I have a pretty face, I have enough money to keep me happy, I work hard and feel successful at what I do. I have great friends, and a great support system and I am also independent enough to not have to rely on others to get done what I need to get done. I am a very stable person." ~ Stephanie that was found in the lick magazine blog. It is quite interesting how that describes me. I'm not that big on the vomiting part, but I'm not gonna lie I do puke after I eat waaay too much, but then so does everyone else, it's not bulimia. I've spent half my day in hospitals.  First I went to Capital Heath System to get my stitches taken out, the same guy that put them in took them out.  He said that everything looks good and that I'm healing very nicely.  Then I was in the Robert Wood Johnson hospital for my mom.  She just had an operation done today around 1pm.  Everything went fine, but she will be in the hospital until Wednesday so I will be at the hospital again tomorrow.  

<lj-cut text="some notes:">
ER is very depressing, all the convicts, the 14 year old girls with their soon to be 14 kids, the car accident victims, the kids with their scraped knees, the old people who are slowly getting ready to die.  It's all very depressing.

The number one theme for paintings that are in hospitals are flowers.  95% of the paintings in the 2 hospitals were of flowers.  Some of them were actually really nice, and most of them were not tacky at all, but still of flowers.  Regardless I had fun going around analyzing what they were made from "oil paint, watercolor, acrylic paint, print, print..."

Robert Wood Johnson is the nicest hospital I have ever been in.  It's new, it's clean, it's well kept, the people that serve the food are dressed as waiters.  It's all very nice, and a very healthy enviroment, I'm glad my mom is there over any other hospital.

Other then all of that life is great.  I spent most of my free time either sleeping or hanging out with Levi.  Me and him are doing wonderfully, we keep amazing eachother with how amazing we are.  ;)  I'm finally going to admit that it may nto be love, but it's damn fucking close, at least for me it is.  Can't wait till friday when I will once again get to spend the whole day with him, maybe this time we can hang out in a normal place like my bed instead of the backseat of the car.  That would be nice.  

I've gotta get back to work now.  I'm working mon-thur this week, from 8 till 5, well unless I leave early ofcourse.  Teeheee.  I love me.

It's funny to come into work and see everyone of your co-workers sitting around drinking a whole bottle of scotch. For my first hour of work I did absolutely nothing. Cut my last 2 classes today, twas nice. Hung out with Levi before work. It was a bit upsating, a bit tense, a bit uncomfortable. Both of us wanted to tell eachother something, but we couldn't either a. get it out or b. figure out how to say it. But it all ended on a good note. He cares, I care, everything is fine. First he said "I don't know how you can be so perfect and so right for me. And I'm not sure if that's a good thing because every time I feel like this about a person is the time that things suck" for about 15 minutes after that we sat almost silently and I just kept thinking then why don't you just end things here so that you don't get hurt and only have the good memories left but ofcourse I couldn't get myself to say it. I was being kinda cold at ceartin points, but then he was cold to me earlier in the day. He asked how long do I think that we can keep things up the way they are, and I said that I have no idea, I've never been in a relationship like this before. Then I said "I guess when we get tired of eachother." Then when he was leaving the car he hugged me really tight and said "Try not to get tired of me any time soon please." It was very sweet. Now I'm waiting for him to call me. I allready want to leave work and see him.

So I had to research a few issues before work today. One of them is a text from Lullaby "'Embolism, if you ask me,' Nash says. 'You eat a girl out and you blow some air inside her, or if you fuck her too hard, either way you can force air into her bloodstream and the bubble goes right to her heart.'" So I decided to reasearch embolism, and yes it can be an air bubble in the blood stream, that's what it usually is used as medically, and one the air bubble will get to the heart it can kill you, and if doesn't kill you when it's in your heart then it will when it gets to your brain. But embolism does not describe that specific way of getting that air bubble into your blood stream. Still, if that is possible it is quite scary I also researched the thing that my mom said that Levi probably has. She called it a czyrak, and in my polish-english dictionary czyrak translates to "boil; furuncle; abcess; anbury; rising furuncle n : a painful sore with a hard pus-filled core boil n: A painful, circumscribed pus-filled inflammation of the skin and subcutaneous tissue usually caused by a local staphylococcal infection. abscess n: A localized collection of pus in part of the body, formed by tissue disintegration and surrounded by an inflamed area. And then anbury talked about horses and oxen so I'm leaving that one out. The thing on his leg was this inflamed thing that was filled with blood and pus so the definitions, especially boil sound correct. My mom told me that there should be a part of a small rust colored vain like tube inside the sore and he needs to remove that tube for the thing to heal. He can get it out with a simple pair of tweezers. I am so totaly nurse Betty so I'm crashing CF band practice today and bringing my tweezers with me... gotta clean em first. The last research that I did today was on the place that Sherri, Jess, Yanni and I are supposed to visit friday. to read about our destination go here and thank Wird NJ. But unfortinately we might not go because I just found out that CF is playing on friday at Trinity. Kill me, but I can't miss a CF show, you know that.
